## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Ad Monetization Strategy**: Google AdSense **does not allow** ads on pure redirect/interstitial pages. The plan uses a two-pronged approach:
> 1. **AdSense** on content-rich pages (dashboard, homepage, link analytics)
> 2. A **countdown/interstitial page** before redirect вҖ” designed with ad slots that can use AdSense (if enough content) or a third-party CPM network (like Linkvertise or ShrinkEarn) later
> 
> For now, I'll create the ad slot placeholders and banner positions throughout the app. You can plug in your AdSense publisher ID later once approved.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Social Login (Google + Microsoft)**: These require OAuth client credentials:
> - **Google**: A Google Cloud Console project with OAuth 2.0 Client ID
> - **Microsoft**: An Azure AD App Registration with Client ID/Secret
> 
> I'll build the full OAuth flow but use placeholder credentials. You'll need to create these before deployment.

> [!WARNING]
> **React Native Web on Vercel**: The frontend will be built as an Expo SPA (`output: "single"`) deployed to Vercel. This works well for the URL shortener dashboard. The actual short URL redirect (`shrink.ly/abc123`) will be handled by the **backend API on Render**, not the frontend.

