## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Backend (Node.js + Express)

#### [NEW] [package.json](file:///c:/Shrinkly/backend/package.json)
- Express 4, Sequelize 6, pg, nanoid, bcryptjs, jsonwebtoken, passport, passport-google-oauth20, passport-microsoft, helmet, cors, express-rate-limit, express-validator, morgan, dotenv

#### [NEW] [server.js](file:///c:/Shrinkly/backend/src/server.js)
- Express app initialization with middleware stack
- CORS configured for frontend origin
- Rate limiting (100 req/15min for auth, 30 req/min for URL creation)
- Helmet security headers
- Morgan logging
- Short URL redirect endpoint: `GET /:code` вҶ’ looks up URL, records click, redirects or returns interstitial page URL

#### [NEW] Database Models
- **User.js**: Email, password hash, OAuth provider fields, timestamps
- **Url.js**: Short code (nanoid, 7 chars), original URL, click counter, expiry, active flag
- **Click.js**: IP, user agent, referrer, country (from IP), device type, timestamp

#### [NEW] Auth System
- `POST /api/auth/signup` вҖ” Email + password registration with validation
- `POST /api/auth/login` вҖ” Email + password login, returns JWT
- `GET /api/auth/google` вҖ” Google OAuth redirect
- `GET /api/auth/google/callback` вҖ” Google OAuth callback, creates/finds user, returns JWT
- `GET /api/auth/microsoft` вҖ” Microsoft OAuth redirect  
- `GET /api/auth/microsoft/callback` вҖ” Microsoft OAuth callback
- `GET /api/auth/me` вҖ” Get current user from JWT
- `POST /api/auth/logout` вҖ” Invalidate session

#### [NEW] URL Shortener API
- `POST /api/urls` вҖ” Create shortened URL (auth required)
- `GET /api/urls` вҖ” List user's URLs with pagination + search
- `GET /api/urls/:id` вҖ” Get single URL with stats
- `PATCH /api/urls/:id` вҖ” Update URL (title, active status)
- `DELETE /api/urls/:id` вҖ” Soft delete URL
- `GET /api/urls/:id/analytics` вҖ” Detailed click analytics

#### [NEW] Redirect Handler
- `GET /:code` вҖ” Public redirect endpoint
  - Looks up short code
  - Records click asynchronously (non-blocking)
  - Returns JSON with redirect info (frontend handles interstitial ad page)
  - OR direct 302 redirect (configurable)

